00:17:04,190 --> 00:17:06,010
the income of Station 203's riders is compared to

291
00:17:06,069 --> 00:17:07,109
other stations, right?

292
00:17:08,240 --> 00:17:09,329
When we come out to work,

293
00:17:09,349 --> 00:17:10,420
when we take on a job,

294
00:17:10,660 --> 00:17:11,660
it's to make money.

295
00:17:12,150 --> 00:17:14,300
You can't be opposing against the mainstream.

296
00:17:15,980 --> 00:17:17,400
Do you know how much pressure

297
00:17:17,400 --> 00:17:19,069
a delivery rider faces in a day?

298
00:17:19,130 --> 00:17:21,260
Running on the streets day and night,

299
00:17:21,420 --> 00:17:22,980
only to be scolded by customers and merchants,

300
00:17:23,000 --> 00:17:24,560
and also by the pedestrians on the road.

301
00:17:24,589 --> 00:17:26,800
If there's even one order cancellation, bad review, or complaint,

302
00:17:26,880 --> 00:17:27,680
the company imposes a penalty.

303
00:17:27,680 --> 00:17:28,640
What can the delivery riders do?

304
00:17:28,680 --> 00:17:30,180
Do they deserve to be treated as less than human?

305
00:17:30,200 --> 00:17:31,860
Then what do you expect the company to do?

306
00:17:31,880 --> 00:17:33,670
If we're slower than others,

307
00:17:33,700 --> 00:17:36,070
if merchants and customers are dissatisfied with us,

308
00:17:36,090 --> 00:17:37,900
how can we compete with others?

309
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,120
Competition, competition.

310
00:17:39,360 --> 00:17:41,330
Those two words are enough to give me a headache!

311
00:17:41,570 --> 00:17:42,660
The market is so big.

312
00:17:42,690 --> 00:17:44,080
Must we fight for first place?

313
00:17:44,110 --> 00:17:45,960
Do we really have to fight to death over this?

314
00:17:46,700 --> 00:17:48,390
We grew up by the canal.

315
00:17:48,690 --> 00:17:50,070
There are so many ships in the canal.

316
00:17:50,070 --> 00:17:50,880
Some ships sail fast,

317
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:51,790
some sail slow.

318
00:17:51,790 --> 00:17:53,640
I've never seen a slow-moving ship get eliminated.

319
00:17:53,640 --> 00:17:55,910
That's because they have different shipping lanes.

320
00:17:57,130 --> 00:17:59,240
Now we're in the same lane.

321
00:18:00,240 --> 00:18:01,640
You may not have personally experienced

322
00:18:01,660 --> 00:18:02,730
the all-out business war in the past two years,

323
00:18:02,790 --> 00:18:03,920
but I have.

324
00:18:04,650 --> 00:18:06,440
Do you know how many companies

325
00:18:06,440 --> 00:18:08,430
went bankrupt in that competition?

326
00:18:08,820 --> 00:18:11,030
The reason Bee survived is due to

327
00:18:11,170 --> 00:18:14,230
the joint efforts of hundreds of thousands of employees and delivery riders.

328
00:18:14,570 --> 00:18:16,770
Once we fail in the competition,

329
00:18:17,010 --> 00:18:19,510
hundreds of thousands of people will instantly lose their jobs.

330
00:18:20,210 --> 00:18:21,730
I believe at that time,

331
00:18:21,980 --> 00:18:23,030
no one will care about

332
00:18:23,030 --> 00:18:25,100
your concern and sympathy for them.

333
00:18:25,220 --> 00:18:26,790
They will only complain about

334
00:18:26,860 --> 00:18:28,730
the management's incompetence!

335
00:18:32,740 --> 00:18:34,730
I believe everyone is aware of

336
00:18:32,980 --> 00:18:36,980
[To be self-aware, to self-improve, to self-enhance, to self-develop]

337
00:18:35,210 --> 00:18:37,220
the current situation of Station 203.

338
00:18:37,240 --> 00:18:38,380
I'm here today

339
00:18:38,410 --> 00:18:39,670
for nothing else

340
00:18:40,060 --> 00:18:41,280
but to change the rules.

341
00:18:41,460 --> 00:18:43,380
Starting from this month,

342
00:18:43,800 --> 00:18:44,730
Station 203

343
00:18:44,760 --> 00:18:46,920
must align and keep up

344
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,920
with other areas.

345
00:18:47,940 --> 00:18:48,690
The goals are to

346
00:18:48,750 --> 00:18:51,000
ensure that the delay rate stays below 5%,

347
00:18:51,490 --> 00:18:53,290
and receive no negative reviews or complaints.

348
00:18:53,330 --> 00:18:54,440
If this is achieved,

349
00:18:54,520 --> 00:18:55,690
performance bonuses will be doubled.

350
00:18:57,340 --> 00:18:58,770
If this is not achieved,

351
00:18:59,780 --> 00:19:01,080
Station 203

352
00:19:01,400 --> 00:19:02,800
will be dissolved immediately

353
00:19:03,030 --> 00:19:05,230
and merged with Stations 202 and 204.

354
00:19:05,580 --> 00:19:06,100
Additionally,

355
00:19:09,390 --> 00:19:11,710
the delivery rider with the lowest number of orders

356
00:19:12,530 --> 00:19:13,560
will be fired immediately.

357
00:19:39,310 --> 00:19:40,550
This place is not bad.

358
00:19:43,120 --> 00:19:44,600
Boss, one bowl of noodles, please.

359
00:19:44,630 --> 00:19:45,670
To go.

360
00:19:45,690 --> 00:19:46,250
Okay.

361
00:19:48,170 --> 00:19:49,000
Bro?

362
00:19:50,830 --> 00:19:51,700
Here to pick up an order?

363
00:19:51,930 --> 00:19:53,440
No, I'm done for the day.

364
00:19:53,650 --> 00:19:55,780
I was thinking of getting a bowl of noodles to tide me over.

365
00:19:55,890 --> 00:19:57,050
Come have a drink.

366
00:19:57,680 --> 00:19:58,590
No thanks.

367
00:19:58,620 --> 00:20:01,010
I have to give a summary report to the higher-ups later.

368
00:20:01,180 --> 00:20:01,860
Come on.

369
00:20:02,390 --> 00:20:03,420
Have a drink.

370
00:20:03,700 --> 00:20:04,870
One drink won't hurt.

371
00:20:10,360 --> 00:20:11,780
Cheers.

372
00:20:12,510 --> 00:20:13,180
Cheers.

373
00:20:19,010 --> 00:20:20,810
Here, eat up.

374
00:20:22,360 --> 00:20:23,610
These have been grilled.

375
00:20:27,270 --> 00:20:27,830
Bro.

376
00:20:29,360 --> 00:20:31,040
You don't have to feel bad.

377
00:20:31,370 --> 00:20:33,700
Personally, we understand your good intentions.

378
00:20:34,070 --> 00:20:35,900
Everyone sings praises of you as a person.

379
00:20:35,930 --> 00:20:38,200
I'll get angry at anyone who says otherwise.

380
00:20:40,930 --> 00:20:42,220
Back then in the karaoke room,

381
00:20:42,540 --> 00:20:44,270
when I was being bullied by a room full of customers,

382
00:20:44,720 --> 00:20:45,550
you jumped in to help me with

383
00:20:45,550 --> 00:20:46,720
the drinking when you couldn't stand it,

384
00:20:46,740 --> 00:20:47,790
only to end up getting beaten.

385
00:20:47,790 --> 00:20:48,510
Of course.

386
00:20:48,960 --> 00:20:50,000
I'm your boss and you're my employee.

387
00:20:50,000 --> 00:20:51,720
How could I just watch you get bullied?

388
00:20:53,040 --> 00:20:53,600
Bro.

389
00:20:55,080 --> 00:20:56,920
All of us are aware of your kindness.

390
00:20:57,460 --> 00:20:58,850
But you're just...

391
00:20:59,160 --> 00:21:00,180
too nice.

392
00:21:00,460 --> 00:21:01,940
You're always thinking about what's best for us,

393
00:21:01,960 --> 00:21:03,240
but it's overly...

394
00:21:06,060 --> 00:21:06,930
It's a bit unrealistic...

395
00:21:07,630 --> 00:21:08,510
and disconnected from reality.

396
00:21:09,510 --> 00:21:10,670
You think I'm wrong too?

397
00:21:10,690 --> 00:21:11,740
You're not wrong.

398
00:21:11,830 --> 00:21:12,750
Mr. Xie was wrong.

399
00:21:15,210 --> 00:21:16,860
Then why don't you support me?

400
00:21:17,240 --> 00:21:18,030
We're poor.

401
00:21:19,790 --> 00:21:20,720
We're terrified of being poor.

402
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:23,780
Bro.

403
00:21:24,350 --> 00:21:25,600
In our line of work,

404
00:21:25,850 --> 00:21:27,720
we work from dawn to dusk,

405
00:21:27,750 --> 00:21:29,070
and if we see a few hundred more

406
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:30,440
in our account when we get home,

407
00:21:30,630 --> 00:21:31,670
that makes us happy.

408
00:21:32,010 --> 00:21:33,680
No matter how hard or tiring the work is,

409
00:21:34,130 --> 00:21:35,680
seeing the money in our wallet increase

410
00:21:35,700 --> 00:21:36,940
gives us peace of mind.

411
00:21:39,280 --> 00:21:39,830
Bro.

412
00:21:40,870 --> 00:21:42,090
Let me put it bluntly.

413
00:21:42,700 --> 00:21:44,000
Take me as an example.

414
00:21:44,250 --> 00:21:45,920
If anyone tries to stop me from making money,

415
00:21:46,310 --> 00:21:47,790
I'll get angry with them,

416
00:21:49,070 --> 00:21:50,440
even if they truly mean well for me.

417
00:21:55,560 --> 00:21:56,680
Aren't you afraid of working yourself to death?

418
00:22:00,870 --> 00:22:02,070
If I really can't take it anymore,

419
00:22:02,510 --> 00:22:03,510
I'll just lie down.

420
00:22:05,350 --> 00:22:06,410
It's still better than dying poor.

421
00:22:15,490 --> 00:22:18,000
A few years ago, before I came to Beijing,

422
00:22:18,070 --> 00:22:19,350
I was full of ambition.

423
00:22:19,600 --> 00:22:22,100
I thought since I was capable, smart and diligent.

424
00:22:22,120 --> 00:22:24,280
I thought I'd make something of myself in just a few years.

425
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:26,720
But now, after all this time,

426
00:22:27,260 --> 00:22:28,700
I still have nothing.

427
00:22:29,150 --> 00:22:30,690
Every day, I still have to squeeze onto buses

428
00:22:30,990 --> 00:22:31,680
and subways,

429
00:22:32,270 --> 00:22:33,280
and sleep in a basement.

430
00:22:35,960 --> 00:22:37,760
Every time I see the lights

431
00:22:38,820 --> 00:22:39,890
in countless residential areas,

432
00:22:40,570 --> 00:22:41,780
lit up by countless lamps,

433
00:22:42,660 --> 00:22:44,720
I realised not a single one belongs to me.

434
00:22:46,090 --> 00:22:47,370
In Beijing,

435
00:22:48,010 --> 00:22:48,850
people like us

436
00:22:49,340 --> 00:22:51,060
are destined to be a passerby.

437
00:23:14,520 --> 00:23:16,980
If one day

438
00:23:18,020 --> 00:23:20,930
I must leave,

439
00:23:23,090 --> 00:23:24,570
I hope that

440
00:23:26,380 --> 00:23:30,180
people will bury me here.

441
00:24:04,260 --> 00:24:04,780
Come.

442
00:24:04,810 --> 00:24:06,100
Have some tea.

443
00:24:06,350 --> 00:24:07,020
Uncle,

444
00:24:07,100 --> 00:24:08,030
you don't have to be so polite.

445
00:24:08,180 --> 00:24:10,050
Haikuo and I were classmates.

446
00:24:10,200 --> 00:24:11,060
In terms of seniority,

447
00:24:11,090 --> 00:24:12,730
I'm a whole generation after you.

448
00:24:13,830 --> 00:24:15,480
Is Haikuo doing well in Beijing?

449
00:24:15,500 --> 00:24:16,220
Quite well.

450
00:24:16,250 --> 00:24:18,530
He's a programmer in the same company as Wanghe.

451
00:24:18,550 --> 00:24:19,390
Which company?

452
00:24:20,380 --> 00:24:21,050
It's called...

453
00:24:21,070 --> 00:24:21,750
Bee.

454
00:24:22,120 --> 00:24:23,120
The food delivery one.

455
00:24:24,050 --> 00:24:25,070
That's a big company

456
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,320
worth tens of billions.

457
00:24:26,350 --> 00:24:28,070
It looks like Haikuo is thriving.

458
00:24:28,880 --> 00:24:30,590
No matter how much money there is, it has nothing to do with them.

459
00:24:30,610 --> 00:24:31,880
It's not theirs anyway.

460
00:24:32,360 --> 00:24:33,400
Can't compare to you,

461
00:24:33,430 --> 00:24:34,480
right?

462
00:24:34,590 --> 00:24:35,880
I'm just a small business owner.

463
00:24:35,900 --> 00:24:36,990
I haven't seen much of the world.

464
00:24:37,020 --> 00:24:39,410
I am just doing some small local business.

465
00:24:39,820 --> 00:24:40,450
But,

466
00:24:40,900 --> 00:24:41,960
I came today

467
00:24:42,120 --> 00:24:44,350
to discuss a great opportunity with you, Uncle.

468
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,240
You see,

469
00:24:46,420 --> 00:24:47,550
with our Grand Canal

470
00:24:47,550 --> 00:24:50,030
becoming a World Heritage Site,

471
00:24:50,300 --> 00:24:52,150
Huaiyang cuisine is in high demand.

472
00:24:52,500 --> 00:24:53,250
A few days ago,

473
00:24:53,280 --> 00:24:54,930
the city leaders gave me an idea.

474
00:24:55,220 --> 00:24:57,020
They want to establish

475
00:24:57,110 --> 00:24:59,660
a Huaiyang cuisine heritage center in the city.

476
00:25:02,360 --> 00:25:03,950
That's a great idea.

477
00:25:04,250 --> 00:25:05,070
But I said,

478
00:25:05,100 --> 00:25:06,830
having the place without the right people won't work.

479
00:25:06,860 --> 00:25:09,350
We need to invite a master in Huaiyang cuisine.

480
00:25:09,370 --> 00:25:10,930
But throughout Honghuai,

481
00:25:11,250 --> 00:25:14,230
you're the only Huaiyang cuisine master we can count on.

482
00:25:14,890 --> 00:25:16,640
We want to invite you to come out of retirement

483
00:25:16,670 --> 00:25:18,260
and teach at the center.

484
00:25:18,280 --> 00:25:19,280
Only with your presence

485
00:25:19,310 --> 00:25:21,980
will this heritage center possess real value.

486
00:25:22,350 --> 00:25:23,550
We're thinking

487
00:25:23,570 --> 00:25:25,330
of moving this century-old By the Canal

488
00:25:25,360 --> 00:25:26,890
into the city

489
00:25:26,960 --> 00:25:29,170
and bring Huaiyang cuisine to greater heights

490
00:25:29,920 --> 00:25:32,910
by allowing more people to enjoy your culinary skills.

491
00:25:41,980 --> 00:25:46,010
[By the Canal]

492
00:25:44,050 --> 00:25:45,060
Master Zhou.

493
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:46,530
Auntie.

494
00:25:46,550 --> 00:25:47,590
Long time no see.

495
00:25:49,260 --> 00:25:50,080
It's me,

496
00:25:50,210 --> 00:25:51,450
a classmate of Xingchi.

497
00:25:51,480 --> 00:25:52,030
Xing...

498
00:25:52,480 --> 00:25:53,520
Liang.

499
00:25:56,440 --> 00:25:57,820
Ah, Liang.

500
00:25:57,900 --> 00:26:00,170
I heard you're a big boss now.

501
00:26:00,220 --> 00:26:01,410
No, no.

502
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,410
What brings you to Flower Street today?

503
00:26:03,680 --> 00:26:05,410
I came to invite Uncle Zhou,

504
00:26:05,440 --> 00:26:05,960
no,

505
00:26:06,420 --> 00:26:07,450
Master Zhou to come out of retirement

506
00:26:07,480 --> 00:26:09,270
to collaborate on a

507
00:26:09,270 --> 00:26:11,420
Huaiyang cuisine heritage center in the city.

508
00:26:13,300 --> 00:26:14,600
Alright, Uncle.

509
00:26:14,770 --> 00:26:15,810
I'll be going now.

510
00:26:15,840 --> 00:26:16,640
Please think it over.

511
00:26:16,660 --> 00:26:17,530
I'll wait for your response.

512
00:26:17,560 --> 00:26:18,880
Okay.

513
00:26:18,900 --> 00:26:19,420
Auntie,

514
00:26:19,480 --> 00:26:20,340
see you around.

515
00:26:20,480 --> 00:26:21,160
Alright.

516
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:21,720
I'll be going now, Uncle.

517
00:26:21,720 --> 00:26:22,350
Okay.

518
00:26:22,370 --> 00:26:23,510
Take care.

519
00:26:23,690 --> 00:26:25,040
[By the Canal]

520
00:26:26,670 --> 00:26:28,160
A heritage center?

521
00:26:28,420 --> 00:26:29,480
Master Zhou,

522
00:26:29,650 --> 00:26:30,870
this is great news.

523
00:26:30,900 --> 00:26:32,200
Your business is growing.

524
00:26:35,000 --> 00:26:35,550
Yes.

525
00:26:43,580 --> 00:26:44,470
You're awake?

526
00:26:46,940 --> 00:26:47,750
Here, let me.

527
00:26:47,770 --> 00:26:48,380
I'll do it.

528
00:26:50,730 --> 00:26:52,040
I fell asleep.

529
00:26:53,730 --> 00:26:55,030
Dad, let me tell you something.

530
00:26:55,030 --> 00:26:56,200
You can't sleep out here anymore.

531
00:26:57,400 --> 00:26:58,640
